"LongComments":{
"-2147483647":{
"Text":"Disassembly of Applesoft II BASIC, as found in the Apple ][+.\r\n\r\nThis project is a conversion of Bob Sander-Cederlof\u0027s \"S-C DocuMentor: Applesoft\", with minor edits.  See http://www.txbobsc.com/scsc/scdocumentor/ for the original disassembly listing.\r\n\r\nChanges from the original include conversion of comments to mixed-case, correction of typographical errors, and general reformatting to fit SourceGen\u0027s constraints.  Some text has been changed to fit personal preference (e.g. PTR vs. PNTR for \"pointer\").  In cases where an operand expression is too complex, the original can be found in the comment field (look for occurrences of \"should be\").  It is likely some errors have been introduced; please consult the original material when in doubt.\r\n\r\nApplesoft is copyright by Microsoft and Apple Computer.\r\nApple ][+ ROM image obtained from AppleWin (Apple2_Plus.rom).\r\n*\r\nProject created by Andy McFadden. Requires 6502bench SourceGen v1.10.\r\nCreated 2019/10/27\r\nLast updated 2025/08/03\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4096":{
"Text":"DOS and monitor call BASIC at $E000 and $E003",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2160":{
"Text":"END statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2158":{
"Text":"STOP statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"128":{
"Text":"No direct pointer for $C0-C7: TAB(, TO, FN, SPC(, THEN, AT, NOT, STEP.  Math operation addresses are below, in MATHTBL.\r\n\r\nAdditional functions follow. Addresses are the actual entry points, unadjusted.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"0":{
"Text":"Branch table for tokens.  Entries are (address-1).",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1894":{
"Text":"FOR statement\r\n\r\nFOR pushes 18 bytes on the stack:\r\n  2 - TXTPTR\r\n  2 - line number\r\n  5 - initial (current) FOR variable value\r\n  1 - step sign\r\n  5 - step value\r\n  2 - address of FOR variable in VARTAB\r\n  1 - FOR token ($81)\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

