"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8802":{
"Text":"SPEED= statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2630":{
"Text":"LET statement\r\n\r\nLET \u003cvar\u003e = \u003cexp\u003e\r\n\u003cvar\u003e = \u003cexp\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2366":{
"Text":"GOTO statement\r\n\r\nAlso used by RUN and GOSUB\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2322":{
"Text":"RUN statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2505":{
"Text":"IF statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2121":{
"Text":"RESTORE statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2337":{
"Text":"GOSUB statement\r\n\r\nLeaves 7 bytes on stack:\r\n  2 - return address (NEWSTT)\r\n  2 - TXTPTR\r\n  2 - line #\r\n  1 - GOSUB token ($B0)\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2524":{
"Text":"REM statement\r\n\r\nOr false IF statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2540":{
"Text":"ON statement\r\n\r\n  ON \u003cexp\u003e GOTO \u003clist\u003e\r\n  ON \u003cexp\u003e GOSUB \u003clist\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6020":{
"Text":"WAIT statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2249":{
"Text":"LOAD statement\r\n\r\nReads a program from cassette tape.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2224":{
"Text":"SAVE statement\r\n\r\nWrites program on cassette tape.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4883":{
"Text":"DEF statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6011":{
"Text":"POKE statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2773":{
"Text":"PRINT statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2198":{
"Text":"CONT statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1701":{
"Text":"LIST statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1642":{
"Text":"CLEAR statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2976":{
"Text":"GET statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1609":{
"Text":"NEW statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7056":{
"Text":"SGN statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7203":{
"Text":"INT statement\r\n\r\nUses QINT to convert FAC to integer form, and then refloats the integer.\r\n\u003c\u003c\u003c A faster approach would simply clear the fractional bits by zeroing them. \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7087":{
"Text":"ABS statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4830":{
"Text":"FRE statement\r\n\r\nCollects garbage and returns # bytes of memory left.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1042":{
"Text":"Handle an error\r\n\r\n  X = offset in error message table\r\n  ERRFLG \u003e 128 if \"on err\" turned on\r\n  CURLIN+1 = $ff if in direct mode\r\n\r\nEntry for SCRN( statement in func table points here.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4045":{
"Text":"PDL statement\r\n\r\n\u003c\u003c\u003c note: arg \u003c 4 is not checked \u003e\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4863":{
"Text":"POS statement\r\n\r\nReturns current line position from MON_CH.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7821":{
"Text":"SQR statement\r\n\r\n\u003c\u003c\u003c Unfortunately, rather than a Newton-Raphson iteration, Applesoft uses exponentiation SQR(x) = x^.5 \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8110":{
"Text":"RND statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6465":{
"Text":"LOG statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7945":{
"Text":"EXP statement\r\n\r\nFAC = E ^ FAC\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8170":{
"Text":"COS statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8177":{
"Text":"SIN statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8250":{
"Text":"TAN statement\r\n\r\nCompute TAN(x) = SIN(x) / COS(x)\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8350":{
"Text":"ATN statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5988":{
"Text":"PEEK statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5846":{
"Text":"LEN statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5061":{
"Text":"STR$ statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5895":{
"Text":"VAL statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5861":{
"Text":"ASC statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5702":{
"Text":"CHR$ statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5722":{
"Text":"LEFT$ statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5766":{
"Text":"RIGHT$ statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5777":{
"Text":"MID$ statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"178":{
"Text":"Math operator branch table\r\n\r\nOne-byte precedence code, followed by two-byte address - 1\r\n\r\nP_OR   $46  \"or\" is lowest precedence\r\nP_AND  $50\r\nP_REL  $64  relational operators\r\nP_ADD  $79  binary + and -\r\nP_MUL  $7B  * and /\r\nP_PWR  $7D  exponentiation\r\nP_NEQ  $7F  unary - and comparison =\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"208":{
"Text":"Token name table",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"608":{
"Text":"Error messages\r\n\r\n(The code uses error message constants that are defined by subtracting the start of the table from the address of the error.  Currently no way to do that in SourceGen, so the constants are project symbols instead.)",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"869":{
"Text":"Called by NEXT and FOR to scan through the stack for a frame with the same variable.\r\n\r\n  FORPNT = address of variable if FOR or NEXT\r\n         = $xxFF if called from RETURN\r\n           \u003c\u003c\u003c BUG: should be $FFxx \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n\r\n  returns .NE. if variable not found,\r\n          X = stack ptr after skipping all frames\r\n\r\n          .EQ. if variable found\r\n          X = stack ptr of frame found\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"915":{
"Text":"Move block of memory up\r\n\r\n  On entry:\r\n    (Y,A) = HIGHDS = destination end + 1\r\n    LOWTR = lowest address of source\r\n    HIGHTR = highest source address + 1\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"982":{
"Text":"Check if enough room left on stack for FOR, GOSUB, or expression evaluation.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"995":{
"Text":"Check if enough room between arrays and strings.\r\n\r\n  (Y,A) = addr arrays need to grow to\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1005":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1073":{
"Text":"Print string at (Y,A)\r\nPrint current line # unless in direct mode\r\nFall into warm restart",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1084":{
"Text":"Warm restart entry\r\n\r\nCome here from monitor by Ctrl+C, 0G, 3D0G, or E003G.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1191":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1205":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1258":{
"Text":"Copy line into program.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1266":{
"Text":"Clear all variables.  Re-establish all forward links.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1324":{
"Text":"Read a line, and strip off sign bits.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1369":{
"Text":"Tokenize the input line.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1424":{
"Text":"Search token name table for match, starting with current char from input line.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1483":{
"Text":"Store character or token in output line.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1513":{
"Text":"Handle literal (between quotes) or remark, by copying chars up to ENDCHR.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1529":{
"Text":"Advance pointer to next token name.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1552":{
"Text":"end of line",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1562":{
"Text":"Search for line\r\n\r\n  LINNUM = line # to find\r\n  if not found: carry = 0\r\n                LOWTR points at next line\r\n  if found:     carry = 1\r\n                LOWTR points at line\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1637":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1667":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1687":{
"Text":"Set TXTPTR to beginning of program.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1967":{
"Text":"STEP phrase of FOR statement.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2002":{
"Text":"Perform NEXT statement.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2053":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2088":{
"Text":"Execute a statement\r\n\r\n  A-reg is first char of statement\r\n  Carry is set\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2131":{
"Text":"Set DATPTR to (Y,A)\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2136":{
"Text":"See if Ctrl+C typed\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2456":{
"Text":"add Y-reg to TXTPTR\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2467":{
"Text":"Scan ahead to next \u0027:\u0027 or EOL",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2572":{
"Text":"Convert line number\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2592":{
"Text":"\u003c\u003c\u003c DANGEROUS CODE \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n\r\nNote that if A-reg = $AB on the line above, ON_1 will compare = and cause a catastrophic jump to $22D9 (for GOTO), or other locations for other calls to LINGET.\r\n\r\nYou can see this if you first put BRK in $22D9, then type \"GO TO 437761\".\r\n\r\nAny value from 437760 through 440319 will cause the problem.  ($AB00-ABFF)\r\n\r\n\u003c\u003c\u003c DANGEROUS CODE \u003e\u003e\u003e",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2659":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2679":{
"Text":"Real variable = expression\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2683":{
"Text":"Install string, descriptor address is at FAC+3,4\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2721":{
"Text":"string not yet in string area, and descriptor is a variable\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2819":{
"Text":"Tab to next comma column\r\n\u003c\u003c\u003c note bug if width of window less than 33 \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2838":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2863":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2874":{
"Text":"Print string at (Y,A)",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2877":{
"Text":"Print string at (FACMO,FACLO)",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2893":{
"Text":"\u003c\u003c\u003c next three lines are useless \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2908":{
"Text":"Print char from A-reg\r\n\r\nNote: POKE 243,32 ($20 in $F3) will convert output to lower case.  This can be cancelled by NORMAL, INVERSE, or FLASH or POKE 243,0.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2929":{
"Text":"Input conversion error: illegal character in numeric field.  Must distinguish between INPUT, READ, and GET\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2951":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3051":{
"Text":"Process input list\r\n\r\n  (Y,X) is address of input data string\r\n  A-reg = value for INPUTFLG: $00 for INPUT\r\n                              $40 for GET\r\n                              $98 for READ\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3431":{
"Text":"Evaluate expression, make sure it is numeric\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3434":{
"Text":"Make sure FAC is numeric\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3436":{
"Text":"Make sure FAC is string\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3437":{
"Text":"Make sure FAC is correct type.\r\n\r\n  if C=0, type must be numeric\r\n  if C=1, type must be string\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3451":{
"Text":"Evaluate the expression at TXTPTR, leaving the result in FAC.  Works for both string and numeric expressions.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3462":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3477":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3533":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3556":{
"Text":"Found one or more relational operators \u003c,=,\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3581":{
"Text":"Stack this operation and call FRMEVL for another one\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3600":{
"Text":"Stack (FAC)\r\n\r\nThree entry points:\r\n  _1, from FRMEVL\r\n  _2, from STEP\r\n  _3, from FOR\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3605":{
"Text":"Enter here from STEP, to push step sign and value\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3616":{
"Text":"Enter here from FOR, with INDEX = step, to push initial value of FOR variable\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3642":{
"Text":"Perform stacked operation.\r\n\r\n  A-reg = precedence byte\r\n  Stack: 1 - CPRMASK\r\n         5 - ARG\r\n         2 - addr of performer\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3651":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3680":{
"Text":"Get element in expression\r\n\r\nGet value of variable or number at TXTPNT, or point to string descriptor if a string, and put in FAC.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3713":{
"Text":"String constant element\r\n\r\n  Set (Y,A) = TXTPTR + carry\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3728":{
"Text":"NOT function\r\n\r\n  if FAC=0, return FAC=1\r\n  if FAC\u003c\u003e0, return FAC=0\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3736":{
"Text":"Comparison for equality (= operator).  Also used to evaluate NOT function.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3762":{
"Text":"Evaluate \"(expression)\"",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3776":{
"Text":"Unless char at TXTPTR = A-reg, syntax error\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3941":{
"Text":"Perform relational operations\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"3965":{
"Text":"String comparison\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4016":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4033":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4067":{
"Text":"PTRGET - general variable scan\r\n\r\nScans variable name at TXTPTR, and searches the VARTAB and ARYTAB for the name.  If not found, create variable of appropriate type.  Return with address in VARPNT and (Y,A).\r\n\r\nActual activity controlled somewhat by two flags:\r\n\r\n  DIMFLG - nonzero if called from DIM\r\n           else = 0\r\n  SUBFLG - = $00\r\n           = $40 if called from GETARYPT\r\n           = $80 if called from DEF FN\r\n           = $C1-DA if called from FN\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4221":{
"Text":"Check if A-reg is ASCII letter A-Z\r\n\r\nReturn carry = 1 if A-Z\r\n             = 0 if not\r\n\r\n\u003c\u003c\u003c NOTE: faster and shorter code: \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n   cmp #\u0027Z\u0027+1  ;compare hi end\r\n   bcs .1      ;above A-Z\r\n   cmp #\u0027A\u0027    ;compare lo end\r\n   rts         ;C=0 if lo, C=1 if A-Z\r\n.1 clc        ;C=0 if hi\r\n   rts\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4231":{
"Text":"Variable not found, so make one\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4252":{
"Text":"Make a new simple variable\r\n\r\nMove arrays up 7 bytes to make room for new variable.  Enter 7-byte variable data in the hole.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4318":{
"Text":"Put address of value of variable in VARPNT and (Y,A)\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4333":{
"Text":"Compute address of first value in array\r\n\r\nARYPNT = LOWTR + #dims*2 + 5\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4350":{
"Text":"\u003c\u003c\u003c meant to be -32768, which would be 9080000000 \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n\u003c\u003c\u003c 1 byte short, so picks up $20 from next instruction \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4354":{
"Text":"Evaluate numeric formula at TXTPTR, converting result to integer 0 \u003c= X \u003c= 32767 in FAC+3,4\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4360":{
"Text":"Convert FAC to integer.  Must be positive and less than 32768.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4364":{
"Text":"Convert FAC to integer.  Must be -32767 \u003c= FAC \u003c= 32767.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4377":{
"Text":"\u003c\u003c\u003c BUG: A=-32768.00049:A%=A is accepted, but PRINT A,A% shows that A=-32768.0005 (ok), A%=32767 (wrong!) \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4382":{
"Text":"Locate array element or create an array\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4386":{
"Text":"Parse the subscript list\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4457":{
"Text":"Search array table for this array name",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4502":{
"Text":"ERROR: bad subscripts\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4505":{
"Text":"ERROR: illegal quantity\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4510":{
"Text":"Found the array\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4536":{
"Text":"Create a new array, unless called from GETARYPT.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4551":{
"Text":"\u003c\u003c\u003c next 3 lines could be written: \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n  LDY #0\r\n  STY STRING2+1\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4619":{
"Text":"Now (A,X) has total # bytes of array elements\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4683":{
"Text":"Find specified array element\r\n\r\nLOWTR,y points at # of dims in array descriptor.  The subscripts are all on the stack as integers.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4713":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4781":{
"Text":"Multiply STRNG2 by (LOWTR,Y) leaving product in (A,X).  Hi-byte also in Y.  Used only by array subscript routines.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4850":{
"Text":"Fall into GIVAYF to float the value.  Note that values over 32767 will return as negative.\r\n\r\nFloat the signed integer in (A,Y).\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4865":{
"Text":"Float Y-reg into FAC, giving value 0-255\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4870":{
"Text":"Check for direct or running mode, giving error if direct mode.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4929":{
"Text":"Common routine for DEF FN and FN, to parse FN and the function name\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"4948":{
"Text":"FN statement",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":true,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5039":{
"Text":"Stack now has 5-byte value of the argument variable, and FNCNAM points at the variable.\r\n\r\nStore five bytes from stack at FNCNAM.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5077":{
"Text":"Get space and make descriptor for string whose address is in FAC+3,4 and whose length is in A-reg",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5085":{
"Text":"Get space and make descriptor for string whose address is in (Y,X) and whose length is in A-reg.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5095":{
"Text":"Build a descriptor for string starting at (Y,A) and terminated by $00 or quotation mark.  Return with descriptor in a temporary and address of descriptor in FAC+3,4.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5101":{
"Text":"Build a descriptor for string starting at (Y,A) and terminated by $00, CHARAC, or ENDCHR.\r\n\r\nReturn with descriptor in a temporary and address of descriptor in FAC+3,4.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5162":{
"Text":"Store descriptor in temporary descriptor stack.\r\n\r\nThe descriptor is now in FAC, FAC+1, FAC+2.  Put address of temp descriptor in FAC+3,4.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5202":{
"Text":"Make space for string at bottom of string space.\r\n\r\n  A-reg = # bytes space to make\r\n\r\nReturn with A-reg same, and (Y,X) = address of space allocated\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5252":{
"Text":"Shove all referenced strings as high as possible in memory (against HIMEM), freeing up space below string area down to STREND.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5272":{
"Text":"Start by collecting temporaries.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5289":{
"Text":"Now collect simple variables.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5314":{
"Text":"Now collect array variables.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5401":{
"Text":"Process a simple variable.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5411":{
"Text":"If string is not empty, check if it is highest.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5458":{
"Text":"Add DSCLEN to ptr in INDEX.  Return with Y=0, ptr also in (X,A).\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5474":{
"Text":"Found highest non-empty string, so move it to top and go back for another.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5527":{
"Text":"Concatenate two strings.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5588":{
"Text":"Get string descriptor pointed at by STRNG1 and move described string to FRESPC.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5602":{
"Text":"Move string at (Y,X) with length in A-reg to destination whose address is in FRESPC,FRESPC+1.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5629":{
"Text":"If FAC is a temporary string, release descriptor.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5632":{
"Text":"If string descriptor pointed to be FAC+3,4 is a temporary string, release it.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5636":{
"Text":"If string descriptor whose address is in (Y,A) is a temporary string, release it.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5685":{
"Text":"Release temporary descriptor if (Y,A) = LASTPT.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5817":{
"Text":"Common setup routine for LEFT$, RIGHT$, MID$: require \")\"; pop return adrs, get descriptor address, get 1st parameter of command\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5852":{
"Text":"If last result is a temporary string, free it.  Make VALTYP numeric, return length in Y-reg.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5877":{
"Text":"Scan to next character and convert expression to single byte in X-reg.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5880":{
"Text":"Evaluate expression at TXTPTR, and convert it to single byte in X-reg.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5883":{
"Text":"Convert FAC to single-byte integer in X-reg.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5938":{
"Text":"\u003c\u003c\u003c That causes a bug if HIMEM=$BFFF, because storing $00 at $C000 is no use; $C000 will always be last char typed, so FIN won\u0027t terminate until it sees a zero at $C010! \u003e\u003e\u003e",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5949":{
"Text":"Copy STRNG2 into TXTPTR.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5958":{
"Text":"Evalute \"EXP1,EXP2\"\r\n\r\n  Convert EXP1 to 16-bit number in LINNUM\r\n  Convert EXP2 to 8-bit number in X-reg\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5964":{
"Text":"Evaluate \",expression\"\r\n\r\n  Convert expression to single byte in X-reg\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"5970":{
"Text":"Convert FAC to a 16-bit value in LINNUM.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7785":{
"Text":"Powers of 10 from 1e8 down to 1, as 32-bit integers, with alternating signs.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6048":{
"Text":"Add 0.5 to FAC\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6055":{
"Text":"FAC = (Y,A) - FAC\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6058":{
"Text":"FAC = ARG - FAC",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6073":{
"Text":"Shift smaller argument more than 7 bits.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6078":{
"Text":"FAC = (Y,A) + FAC\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6081":{
"Text":"FAC = ARG + FAC\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6094":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6185":{
"Text":"Normalize value in FAC.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6222":{
"Text":"Set FAC = 0 (only necessary to zero exponent and sign cells)\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6229":{
"Text":"Add mantissas of FAC and ARG into FAC.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6260":{
"Text":"Finish normalizing FAC.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6272":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6302":{
"Text":"2\u0027s complement of FAC",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6308":{
"Text":"2\u0027s complement of FAC mantissa only",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6342":{
"Text":"Increment FAC mantissa.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6362":{
"Text":"Shift 1,X through 5,X right\r\n  A-reg = negative of shift count\r\n  X-reg = pointer to bytes to be shifted\r\n\r\n  Return with Y-reg=0, carry=0, extension bits in A-reg\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6384":{
"Text":"Main entry to right shift subroutine.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6407":{
"Text":"Enter here for short shifts with no sign extension.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6445":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6527":{
"Text":"FAC = (Y,A) * FAC\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6530":{
"Text":"FAC = ARG * FAC\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6535":{
"Text":"\u003c\u003c\u003c why is line above just \"RTS\"? \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6576":{
"Text":"Multiply ARG by A-reg into RESULT\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6627":{
"Text":"Unpack number at (Y,A) into ARG\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6670":{
"Text":"Add exponents of ARG and FAC (called by FMULT and FDIV).\r\n\r\nAlso check for overflow, and set result sign.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6694":{
"Text":"\u003c\u003c\u003c Crazy to jump way back there!  Same identical code is below!  Instead of BNE .2, JMP STA_IN_FAC_SIGN, only needed BEQ .3 \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6699":{
"Text":"If FAC is positive, give \"overflow\" error.\r\nIf FAC is negative, set FAC=0, pop one return, and RTS.\r\nCalled from EXP function.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6705":{
"Text":"Pop return address and set FAC=0.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6713":{
"Text":"Multiply FAC by 10.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6741":{
"Text":"Divide FAC by 10.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6750":{
"Text":"FAC = ARG / (Y,A)\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6758":{
"Text":"FAC = (Y,A) / FAC\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6761":{
"Text":"FAC = ARG / FAC\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6886":{
"Text":"Copy RESULT into FAC mantissa, and normalize.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6905":{
"Text":"Unpack (Y,A) into FAC.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6942":{
"Text":"Round FAC, store in TEMP2.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6945":{
"Text":"Round FAC, store in TEMP1.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6951":{
"Text":"Round FAC, and store where FORPNT points.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6955":{
"Text":"Round FAC, and store at (Y,X).\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"6995":{
"Text":"Copy ARG into FAC.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7011":{
"Text":"Round FAC and copy to ARG.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7026":{
"Text":"Round FAC using extension byte.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7034":{
"Text":"Increment mantissa and re-normalize if carry.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7042":{
"Text":"Test FAC for zero and sign.\r\n\r\n  FAC \u003e 0, return +1\r\n  FAC = 0, return  0\r\n  FAC \u003c 0, return -1\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7059":{
"Text":"Convert A-reg into FAC, as signed value -128 to +127.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7067":{
"Text":"Float unsigned value in FAC+1,2.\r\n\r\n  X-reg = exponent\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7072":{
"Text":"Float unsigned value in FAC+1,2\r\n\r\n  X-reg = exponent\r\n  C=0 to make value negative\r\n  C=1 to make value positive\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7090":{
"Text":"Compare FAC with packed # at (Y,A).\r\nReturn A=1,0,-1 as (Y,A) is \u003c,=,\u003e FAC.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7092":{
"Text":"Special entry from NEXT processor.  DEST already set up.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7151":{
"Text":"\u003c\u003c\u003c Note that above three lines can be shortened:\r\n  .1 ROR            ;put carry into sign bit\r\n     EOR FAC_SIGN   ;toggle with sign of FAC\r\n\u003e\u003e\u003e",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7154":{
"Text":"Quick integer function.\r\n\r\nConverts fp value in FAC to integer value in FAC+1 ... FAC+4, by shifting right with sign extension until fractional bits are out.\r\n\r\nThis subroutine assumes the exponent \u003c 32.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7242":{
"Text":"Convert string to FP value in FAC.\r\n\r\n  String pointed to by TXTPTR\r\n  First char already scanned by CHRGET\r\n  A-reg=first char, C=0 if digit\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7303":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7320":{
"Text":"Found a decimal point.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7326":{
"Text":"A second decimal point is taken as a terminator to the numeric string.\r\n\"A=11..22\" will give a syntax error, because it is two numbers with no operator between.\r\n\"PRINT 11..22\" gives no error, because it is just the concatenation of two numbers.\r\n\r\nNumber terminated, adjust exponent now.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7361":{
"Text":"Accumulate a digit into FAC.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7381":{
"Text":"Add A-reg to FAC.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7400":{
"Text":"Accumulate digit of exponent.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7449":{
"Text":"Print \"IN \u003cLINE #\u003e\".",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7460":{
"Text":"Print (A,X) as decimal integer.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7470":{
"Text":"Convert FAC to string, and print it.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7473":{
"Text":"Print string starting at (Y,A).\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7476":{
"Text":"Convert FAC to string starting at stack.\r\nReturn with (Y,A) pointing at string.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7478":{
"Text":"STR$ function enters here, with Y-reg=0 so that result string starts at stack-1 (this is used as a flag).",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7522":{
"Text":"Adjust until 1e8 \u003c= FAC \u003c 1e9.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7564":{
"Text":"FAC+1 ... FAC+4 is now in integer form with power of ten adjustment in TMPEXP.\r\n\r\nIf -10 \u003c TMPEXP \u003e 1, print in decimal form.  Otherwise, print in exponential form.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7613":{
"Text":"Now divide by powers of ten to get successive digits.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7703":{
"Text":"Nine digits have been stored in string.  Now look back and lop off trailing zeroes and a trailing decimal point.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7831":{
"Text":"Exponentiation operation\r\n\r\nARG ^ FAC = EXP( LOG(ARG) * FAC )\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7888":{
"Text":"Negate value in FAC.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"7989":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8028":{
"Text":"Odd polynomial subroutine\r\n\r\n  F(x) = x * P(x^2)\r\n\r\n  where: x is value in FAC\r\n         (Y,A) points at coefficient table\r\n         first byte of coeff. table is N\r\n         coefficients follow, highest power first\r\n\r\n  P(x^2) computed using normal polynomial subroutine\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8050":{
"Text":"Normal polynomial subroutine\r\n\r\n  P(x) = C(0)*x^n + C(1)*x^(n-1) + ... + C(n)\r\n\r\n  where: x is value in FAC\r\n         (Y,A) points at coefficient table\r\n         first byte of coeff. table is N\r\n         coefficients follow, highest power first\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8340":{
"Text":"\u003c\u003c\u003c next 10 bytes are never referenced \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8202":{
"Text":"FAC = angle as a fraction of a full circle\r\n\r\nNow fold the range into a quarter circle.\r\n\r\n\u003c\u003c\u003c there are much simpler ways to do this \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8227":{
"Text":"if fall thru, range is 0...1/2\r\nif branch here, range is 0...1/4\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8230":{
"Text":"if fall thru, range is -1/2...0\r\nif branch here, range is -1/4...0\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8372":{
"Text":"0 \u003c= x \u003c= 1\r\n0 \u003c= ATN(x) \u003c= PI/8\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8459":{
"Text":"Generic copy of CHRGET subroutine, which is copied into $00B1...00C8 during initialization.\r\n\r\nCornelis Bongers described several improvements to CHRGET in Micro magazine or Call-A.P.P.L.E. (I don\u0027t remember which or exactly when).\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8483":{
"Text":"Initial value for random number, also copied in along with CHRGET, but erroneously:\r\n\u003c\u003c\u003c the last byte is not copied \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8528":{
"Text":"Move generic CHRGET and random seed into place\r\n\r\n\u003c\u003c\u003c Note that loop value is wrong!  The last byte of the random seed is not copied into page zero! \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8540":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8567":{
"Text":"Find high end of RAM\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8684":{
"Text":"Get two values \u003c 48, with comma separator\r\n\r\nCalled for PLOT X,Y\r\n       and HLIN A,B at Y\r\n       and VLIN A,B at X\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8713":{
"Text":"Get \"A,B at C\" values for HLIN and VLIN\r\n\r\nPut smaller of (A,B) in FIRST, and larger of (A,B) in H2 and V2.  Return with X-reg = C-value.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8937":{
"Text":"Routine to handle errors if ONERR GOTO active.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"8943":{
"Text":"\u003c\u003c\u003ccould also have done TXS here; see ONERR correction in Applesoft manual.\u003e\u003e\u003e",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9000":{
"Text":"\u003c\u003c\u003c ONERR correction in manual is easily by CALL -3288, which is $F328 here. \u003e\u003e\u003e",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9202":{
"Text":"Clear screen.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9206":{
"Text":"Fill screen with HGR_BITS.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9233":{
"Text":"Set the hi-res cursor position.\r\n\r\n  (Y,X) = horizontal coordinate (0-279)\r\n  A-reg = vertical coordinate   (0-191)\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9277":{
"Text":"no: 256/7 = 36 rem 4\r\ncarry=1, so ADC #4 is too large; however, ADC #4 clears carry which makes SBC #7 only -6, balancing it out.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9303":{
"Text":"Plot a dot\r\n\r\n  (Y,X) = horizontal position\r\n  A-reg = vertical position\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9317":{
"Text":"Move left or right one pixel.\r\n\r\nIf status is +, move right; if -, move left\r\nIf already at left or right edge, wrap around\r\n\r\nRemember bits in hi-res byte are backwards order:\r\n  byte N  byte N+1\r\nS7654321  SEDCBA98\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9342":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9354":{
"Text":"Move right one pixel.\r\n\r\nIf already at right edge, wrap around.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9359":{
"Text":"Original:  C0 A0 90 88 84 82 81\r\nShifted:   80 40 20 10 08 02 01\r\nEOR #$80:  00 C0 A0 90 88 84 82\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9372":{
"Text":"\"XDRAW\" one bit",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9395":{
"Text":"\"DRAW\" one bit\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9412":{
"Text":"Toggle bit on screen with A-reg.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9416":{
"Text":"Determine where next point will be, and move there.\r\n\r\n  C=0 if no 90 degree rotation\r\n  C=1 rotates 90 degrees\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9422":{
"Text":"  00 - up\r\n  01 - down\r\n  10 - right\r\n  11 - left\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9427":{
"Text":"\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9429":{
"Text":"Move up one pixel\r\n\r\nIf already at top, go to bottom.\r\n\r\nRemember:  Y-coord   HBASH     HBASL\r\n          ABCDEFGH  PPPFGHCD  EABAB000",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9456":{
"Text":"   0000+1011=1011 and carry clear\r\nor 0101+1011=0000 and carry set\r\nor 1010+1011=0101 and carry set\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9477":{
"Text":"Move down one pixel\r\n\r\nIf already at bottom, go to top.\r\n\r\nRemember:  Y-coord   HBASH     HBASL\r\n          ABCDEFGH  PPPFGHCD  EABAB000\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9498":{
"Text":"increment \"AB\" then\r\n0000 --\u003e 0101\r\n0101 --\u003e 1010\r\n1010 --\u003e wrap around to line 0\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9520":{
"Text":"HLINRL\r\n(never called by Applesoft)\r\n\r\nEnter with: (A,X) = DX from current point\r\n            Y-reg = DY from current point",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9530":{
"Text":"Draw line from last plotted point to (A,X),Y\r\n\r\nEnter with: (A,X) = X of target point\r\n            Y-reg = Y of target point\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9596":{
"Text":"Move left or right one pixel.  A-reg bit 6 has direction.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9601":{
"Text":"Draw line now.",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9658":{
"Text":"Table of COS(90*x/16 degrees)*$100 - 1, with one-byte precision, X=0 to 16",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9675":{
"Text":"HFIND - calculates current position of hi-res cursor\r\n(not called by any Applesoft routine)\r\n\r\nCalculate Y-coord from HBASH,L\r\n      and X-coord from HORIZ and HMASK\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9729":{
"Text":"DRAW0\r\n(not called by Applesoft)\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9733":{
"Text":"Draw a shape\r\n\r\n  (Y,X) = shape starting address\r\n  A-reg = rotation ($00-3F)\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9821":{
"Text":"XDRAW0\r\n(not called by Applesoft)\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9825":{
"Text":"XDRAW a shape (same as DRAW, except toggles screen)\r\n\r\n  (Y,X) = shape starting address\r\n  A-reg = rotation ($00-3F)\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"9913":{
"Text":"Get hi-res plotting coordinates (0-279,0-191) from TXTPTR.  Leave registers set up for HPOSN:\r\n\r\n  (Y,X) = X-coord\r\n  A-reg = Y-coord\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"10029":{
"Text":"Set up for DRAW and XDRAW.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"10172":{
"Text":"Called from STORE and RECALL.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"10201":{
"Text":"Called from STORE and RECALL.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"1116":{
"Text":"Handle numbered line.\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0},

"2417":{
"Text":"\u003c\u003c\u003c see \"All About Applesoft\", pages 100,101 \u003e\u003e\u003e\r\n",
"IsFancy":false,
"BoxMode":false,
"MaxWidth":80,
"BackgroundColor":0}},

"Notes":{
},

